<item>
            <title>[HADOOP-9022] Hadoop distcp tool fails to copy file if -m 0 specified</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-9022</link>
                <project id="12310240" key="HADOOP">Hadoop Common</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When trying to copy file using distcp on H23, if -m 0 is specified, distcp will just spawn 0 mapper tasks and the file will not be copied.&lt;br/&gt;
But this used to work before H23, even when -m 0 specified, distcp will always copy the files.&lt;br/&gt;
Checked the code of DistCp.java&lt;br/&gt;
Before the rewrite, it set the number maps at least to 1&lt;br/&gt;
job.setNumMapTasks(Math.max(numMaps, 1));&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But in the newest code, it just takes the input from user:&lt;br/&gt;
job.getConfiguration().set(JobContext.NUM_MAPS,&lt;br/&gt;
                  String.valueOf(inputOptions.getMaxMaps()));&lt;/p&gt;</description>
